00:17:49,880 --> 00:17:51,960
 and grateful before the Lord.

269
00:17:51,960 --> 00:17:55,880
 (speaking in foreign language)

270
00:17:55,880 --> 00:18:08,400
 - And the second blessings that we have in God

271
00:18:08,400 --> 00:18:10,400
 is the blessed salvation.

272
00:18:10,400 --> 00:18:13,560
 In verse seven, "In him we have redemption through his blood.

273
00:18:13,560 --> 00:18:15,200
 The forgiveness of sins

274
00:18:15,200 --> 00:18:18,120
 in accordance with the riches of his grace."

275
00:18:18,120 --> 00:18:22,040
 (speaking in foreign language)

276
00:18:22,040 --> 00:18:26,840
 - So redemption is the ransom paid

277
00:18:26,840 --> 00:18:29,640
 by a slave for his own freedom.

278
00:18:29,640 --> 00:18:33,560
 (speaking in foreign language)

279
00:18:33,560 --> 00:18:37,760
 - And so when God redeems us with a ransom,

280
00:18:37,760 --> 00:18:39,800
 that ransom is Jesus himself.

281
00:18:40,800 --> 00:18:44,720
 (speaking in foreign language)

282
00:18:44,720 --> 00:18:52,880
 - Many people think that they are a free person,

283
00:18:52,880 --> 00:18:56,880
 but the Bible says that all who sins are slaves to sin.

284
00:18:56,880 --> 00:19:00,800
 (speaking in foreign language)

285
00:19:00,800 --> 00:19:10,200
 - We only have freedom in our sins,

286
00:19:10,200 --> 00:19:12,400
 but not freedom from our sins.

287
00:19:12,400 --> 00:19:18,440
 (speaking in foreign language)

288
00:19:18,440 --> 00:19:30,000
 - Only in Christ Jesus, our freedom can be restored.

289
00:19:30,000 --> 00:19:31,320
 If you're not in Jesus,

290
00:19:31,320 --> 00:19:33,320
 you are under the bondage to all kinds of things

291
00:19:33,320 --> 00:19:34,280
 in the world.

292
00:19:34,280 --> 00:19:37,360
 And so come to Jesus and you will have true freedom.

293
00:19:37,360 --> 00:19:41,280
 (speaking in foreign language)

294
00:19:41,280 --> 00:19:46,520
 - Paul then continues,

295
00:19:46,520 --> 00:19:50,120
 "Humanity is redeemed through the blood of Jesus."

296
00:19:50,120 --> 00:19:54,040
 (speaking in foreign language)

297
00:19:54,040 --> 00:20:12,560
 - So in the Old Testament,

298
00:20:12,560 --> 00:20:14,680
 before the Israel worship at the temple,

299
00:20:14,680 --> 00:20:17,480
 the high priest would lay their hands on an animal,

300
00:20:17,480 --> 00:20:20,240
 transferring Israel's sins to the lamb.

301
00:20:20,240 --> 00:20:22,160
 And then the high priest would slaughter it

302
00:20:22,160 --> 00:20:24,680
 and bring his blood into the holy of holies

303
00:20:24,680 --> 00:20:27,400
 so that God can forgive their sins.

304
00:20:27,400 --> 00:20:31,440
 (speaking in foreign language)

305
00:20:31,440 --> 00:20:34,160
 - But could these lambs truly bear our sin?

306
00:20:34,160 --> 00:20:38,080
 (speaking in foreign language)

307
00:20:38,080 --> 00:20:50,440
 - Absolutely no.

308
00:20:50,440 --> 00:20:53,640
 So these lambs cannot bear our sin.

309
00:20:53,640 --> 00:20:57,320
 They only foreshadow Jesus, the one true lamb of God.

310
00:20:57,320 --> 00:21:00,160
 And God prepared the true lamb for his chosen people.

311
00:21:00,160 --> 00:21:06,200
 (speaking in foreign language)

312
00:21:06,200 --> 00:21:19,440
 - So what can we take away from this blessed salvation?

313
00:21:19,440 --> 00:21:21,600
 A lot of times we think of forgiveness of sins

314
00:21:21,600 --> 00:21:23,480
 as something that is easy,

315
00:21:23,480 --> 00:21:26,920
 but the truth is the price is actually pretty costly.

316
00:21:26,920 --> 00:21:31,920
 (speaking in foreign language)

317
00:21:31,920 --> 00:21:40,480
 - What is the most valuable things in our world?

318
00:21:40,480 --> 00:21:43,720
 A mansion, a fancy car, Bitcoin?

319
00:21:43,720 --> 00:21:47,200
 These are all valuable, but they are not the most valuable.

320
00:21:47,200 --> 00:21:51,120
 (speaking in foreign language)

321
00:21:51,120 --> 00:21:59,160
 - My wife always says anything that money can solve

322
00:21:59,160 --> 00:22:00,560
 isn't a big problem.

323
00:22:00,560 --> 00:22:03,440
 What money cannot solve is the real problem.

324
00:22:03,440 --> 00:22:09,120
 (speaking in foreign language)

325
00:22:09,120 --> 00:22:16,000
 - Among all the things that money cannot buy,

326
00:22:16,000 --> 00:22:18,280
 salvation is the most important one

327
00:22:18,280 --> 00:22:20,280
 because Jesus' death is required to pay

328
00:22:20,280 --> 00:22:21,680
 for the wages of our sin.

329
00:22:21,680 --> 00:22:25,600
 (speaking in foreign language)

330
00:22:25,600 --> 00:22:30,120
 - Jesus is the most precious and most honored in the world.

331
00:22:30,120 --> 00:22:35,040
 (speaking in foreign language)

332
00:22:35,040 --> 00:22:38,000
 - And the saddest reality in our life

333
00:22:38,000 --> 00:22:39,920
 is that we live our whole life on earth,

334
00:22:39,920 --> 00:22:42,600
 but we completely miss the most valuable gift

335
00:22:42,600 --> 00:22:44,760
 that is the gift of salvation through Jesus.

336
00:22:44,760 --> 00:22:48,680
 (speaking in foreign language)

337
00:22:48,680 --> 00:22:59,360
 - And the third blessings that we have is the blessed seal.

338
00:22:59,360 --> 00:23:04,920
 (speaking in foreign language)

339
00:23:04,920 --> 00:23:09,920
 - Paul say when you share the truth and believe in Jesus,

340
00:23:09,920 --> 00:23:13,160
 you receive the Holy Spirit as a seal.

341
00:23:13,160 --> 00:23:17,080
 (speaking in foreign language)

342
00:23:17,080 --> 00:23:20,600
 - Seal has several meanings.

343
00:23:20,600 --> 00:23:23,000
 First, it signifies that this thing is real,

344
00:23:23,000 --> 00:23:24,360
 not counterfeit.

345
00:23:24,360 --> 00:23:28,280
 (speaking in foreign language)

346
00:23:28,280 --> 00:23:38,360
 - In most places in the world,

347
00:23:38,360 --> 00:23:41,320
 there will be no legal effects without an actual seal.

348
00:23:41,320 --> 00:23:43,400
 We put our signature on text forms

349
00:23:43,400 --> 00:23:46,680
 or house deeds to validate its authenticity.

350
00:23:46,680 --> 00:23:50,600
 (speaking in foreign language)

351
00:23:50,600 --> 00:24:09,920
 - So the seal of the Holy Spirit on his believers

352
00:24:09,920 --> 00:24:12,600
 means that the blessings of God's election,

353
00:24:12,600 --> 00:24:14,480
 the blessings of Christ's redemption,

354
00:24:14,480 --> 00:24:16,880
 and the blessings of our adoption to sonship,

355
00:24:16,880 --> 00:24:19,240
 they're all true and they're legally binding.

356
00:24:19,240 --> 00:24:24,320
 (speaking in foreign language)

357
00:24:24,320 --> 00:24:38,400
 - A seal also represents ownerships.

358
00:24:38,400 --> 00:24:40,800
 Many farmers, they will put a stamp on their animals

359
00:24:40,800 --> 00:24:43,480
 or tag their ears so that when other people see it,

360
00:24:43,480 --> 00:24:45,960
 they know who these animals belong to.

361
00:24:45,960 --> 00:24:49,880
 (speaking in foreign language)

362
00:24:49,880 --> 00:24:55,440
 - So when the Holy Spirit puts his stamps on the believers,

363
00:24:55,440 --> 00:24:58,840
 that means that we belong to God, not to other people.

364
00:24:58,840 --> 00:25:02,760
 (speaking in foreign language)

365
00:25:02,760 --> 00:25:30,760
 - In our today's multicultural context,

366
00:25:30,760 --> 00:25:33,640
 ownership is often labored as hegemony.

367
00:25:33,640 --> 00:25:36,760
 A wife belonging to her husband is called patriarchy.

368
00:25:36,760 --> 00:25:40,360
 A child to the parents is considered as parental control.

369
00:25:40,360 --> 00:25:43,680
 And people belong to God is viewed as divine oppression.

370
00:25:43,680 --> 00:25:45,360
 But this is not true.

371
00:25:45,360 --> 00:25:49,280
 (speaking in foreign language)

372
00:25:49,280 --> 00:26:08,880
 - So when I say that my child belongs to me,

373
00:26:08,880 --> 00:26:11,360
 it means that I will care for and protect them,

374
00:26:11,360 --> 00:26:12,800
 not to oppress them.

375
00:26:12,800 --> 00:26:13,920
 And so in the same way,

376
00:26:13,920 --> 00:26:16,400
 when Paul says that Christians will belong to God,

377
00:26:16,400 --> 00:26:18,440
 it means that God will care for his people,

378
00:26:18,440 --> 00:26:19,520
 not to oppress them.

379
00:26:19,520 --> 00:26:23,440
 (speaking in foreign language)

380
00:26:23,440 --> 00:26:42,200
 - So thirdly, seal also represents security.

381
00:26:42,200 --> 00:26:44,080
 All our important documents will have seal

382
00:26:44,080 --> 00:26:46,800
 to protect its content, right?

383
00:26:46,800 --> 00:26:48,480
 A police would tap off areas with seal,

384
00:26:48,480 --> 00:26:50,520
 meaning that this area is blocked

385
00:26:50,520 --> 00:26:52,720
 and that you are not allowed to tamper it.

386
00:26:52,720 --> 00:26:55,120
 And so the seal of the Holy Spirit on God's people

387
00:26:55,120 --> 00:26:57,600
 means that God will protect his people

388
00:26:57,600 --> 00:27:00,240
 until the day when we meet him face to face.

389
00:27:00,240 --> 00:27:05,440
 (speaking in foreign language)

390
00:27:05,440 --> 00:27:10,480
 - And so our salvation in Jesus is secure.

391
00:27:10,480 --> 00:27:24,400
 (speaking in foreign language)

392
00:27:24,400 --> 00:27:27,120
 - So what can we take away from these blessings

393
00:27:27,120 --> 00:27:29,440
 of the seal of the Holy Spirit?

394
00:27:29,440 --> 00:27:33,080
 As Christian, we face all sorts of worldly temptation,

395
00:27:33,080 --> 00:27:35,760
 different difficulties, challenge, and failures.

396
00:27:35,760 --> 00:27:37,880
 And no one can live our Christian life

397
00:27:37,880 --> 00:27:41,320
 from the beginning to the end by relying on themselves.

398
00:27:41,320 --> 00:27:49,480
 (speaking in foreign language)

399
00:27:49,480 --> 00:27:51,360
 - Can you be sure that the day that you die,

400
00:27:51,360 --> 00:27:53,400
 you will still believe in Jesus?

401
00:27:53,400 --> 00:27:54,520
 Or have you ever doubted

402
00:27:54,520 --> 00:27:57,680
 whether you can persevere to the end?

403
00:27:57,680 --> 00:28:09,600
 (speaking in foreign language)

404
00:28:09,600 --> 00:28:14,200
 - The world is always luring us away from Jesus all the time.

405
00:28:14,200 --> 00:28:16,760
 And as Christians, we experience peaks and valleys

406
00:28:16,760 --> 00:28:20,520
 in our faith as well.

407
00:28:20,520 --> 00:28:31,160
 (speaking in foreign language)

408
00:28:31,160 --> 00:28:34,200
 - But thank God that he knows we are weak sometimes.

409
00:28:34,200 --> 00:28:37,760
 And thank God that he knows that the temptation

410
00:28:37,760 --> 00:28:42,840
 from the world sometimes can pull us away from him.

411
00:28:42,840 --> 00:28:54,880
 (speaking in foreign language)

412
00:28:54,880 --> 00:28:56,640
 - And when we are sealed by the Holy Spirit,

413
00:28:56,640 --> 00:28:59,560
 the Spirit becomes the guarantee of our salvation,

414
00:28:59,560 --> 00:29:02,920
 not our own feelings.

415
00:29:02,920 --> 00:29:15,080
 (speaking in foreign language)

416
00:29:15,080 --> 00:29:18,080
 - So how can we be sure that we won't fall away?

417
00:29:18,080 --> 00:29:20,480
 The Spirit of the Lord guarantees it.

418
00:29:20,480 --> 00:29:22,840
 So when we are weak, are we willing to rely

419
00:29:22,840 --> 00:29:25,480
 on the Holy Spirit instead of ourselves?

420
00:29:25,480 --> 00:29:35,200
 (speaking in foreign language)

421
00:29:35,200 --> 00:29:37,960
 - So let's conclude our passage today.

422
00:29:37,960 --> 00:29:40,160
 Our passage tells us that only in Christ Jesus,

423
00:29:40,160 --> 00:29:42,000
 we are truly blessed.

424
00:29:42,000 --> 00:29:59,280
 (speaking in foreign language)

425
00:29:59,280 --> 00:30:02,160
 - So in Christ, bless you means that God has chosen you

426
00:30:02,160 --> 00:30:04,160
 and given your life true meaning.

427
00:30:04,160 --> 00:30:07,600
 In Christ, bless you means that Jesus has redeemed you

428
00:30:07,600 --> 00:30:09,880
 and your life is worth everything to him.

429
00:30:09,880 --> 00:30:12,520
 And in Christ, bless you means that the Holy Spirit

430
00:30:12,520 --> 00:30:16,440
 has sealed you and your life is secure in him.

431
00:30:16,440 --> 00:30:22,200
 (speaking in foreign language)

432
00:30:22,200 --> 00:30:25,280
 - So the questions that I have for all of us is this.

433
00:30:25,280 --> 00:30:27,560
 Are you living in this blessing?

434
00:30:27,560 --> 00:30:29,840
 (speaking in foreign language)

435
00:30:29,840 --> 00:30:30,680
 - Let's pray.

436
00:30:30,680 --> 00:30:36,000
 (speaking in foreign language)

437
00:30:36,000 --> 00:30:38,760
 - Heavenly Father, thank you for giving us your word.

438
00:30:39,640 --> 00:30:48,680
 (speaking in foreign language)

439
00:30:48,680 --> 00:30:51,200
 - We pray for those among us who have not yet received

440
00:30:51,200 --> 00:30:52,800
 or understand these blessings.

441
00:30:52,800 --> 00:30:54,680
 Would you open your eyes to see the need

442
00:30:54,680 --> 00:30:56,440
 for your salvation?

443
00:30:56,440 --> 00:31:05,240
 (speaking in foreign language)

444
00:31:05,240 --> 00:31:07,640
 - For those who already know these blessings,

445
00:31:07,640 --> 00:31:10,960
 help us to cherish them and also give you thanks

446
00:31:10,960 --> 00:31:12,280
 for your grace.

447
00:31:12,280 --> 00:31:14,840
 (speaking in foreign language)

448
00:31:14,840 --> 00:31:16,800
 - In the name of Jesus Christ, amen.

449
00:31:16,800 --> 00:31:21,560
 Okay, thank you, Paul.

450
00:31:21,560 --> 00:31:24,040
 And thank you all for coming.

451
00:31:24,040 --> 00:31:26,040
 We will have some refreshment outside,

452
00:31:26,040 --> 00:31:30,600
 so feel free to stay after and get to know some new people.

453
00:31:30,600 --> 00:31:32,560
 All right, go in peace, UV, your love.

454
00:31:33,560 --> 00:31:36,560
 (people chattering)

455
00:31:36,560 --> 00:31:39,560
 (people chattering)

